ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: yes, I would recommend it to fellows interested in theoretical economics.

You will learn the most important things about integration and measure. It would be a bad idea not to take this class. Prof Garland does a great job teaching it and you will suffer if you do not learn the material early in your career.

The course is very demanding, and I would only recommend it to a student who is very well-prepared for it. Furthermore, I would also point out that the instructor is difficult to understand at times and extremely fast.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: it provided me with tools that will most likely be useful in my future research.
Measure theory is fundamental to probability and appears anywhere integration does. Therefore this course was essential to my research work and future course work.
The coursewas very helpful to learn more about measure theory.
